I've found working with plugins and AMD to be surprisingly easy.  I wrote [use.js](https://github.com/tbranyen/use.js/) to address this problem in the Dojo and RequireJS loaders (might work in the Twitter loader as well).  The concept is loading jQuery as a dependency to any plugin.

Example (in RequireJS):

``` javascript
require.config({
  shim: {
    // Ensure jQuery is loaded before the chosen jQuery plugin
    "chosen.jquery": ["jquery"]
  }
});
```

and then you can load it wherever (the loader should cache after the first execution):

``` javascript
require(["jquery", "chosen.jquery"], function($) {
  /* Chosen plugin is available here. */
});
```

