@kmargaritis I had the same prroblem and I have managed to make it work, but you must change the flight's files to enable this.
First, create a require module for private jquery (jquery that is not in global scope):

```
jquery-private.js
-------------------------
define(['jquery'], function ($) {
    'use strict';
    return $.noConflict( true );
});
```

then, in your require config file, add the paths to `jquery` and `jquery-private` and map the request to `jquery` to route to `jquery-private`.

```
common.js
------------------
requirejs.config({
    baseUrl: 'your/base/path',
    paths: {
        'flight': '../libs/flight',
        'jquery': 'jquery/jquery',
        'jquery-private': '../libs/jquery-private'
    },
    map: {
        // '*' means all modules will get 'jquery-private'
        // for their 'jquery' dependency.
        '*': { 'jquery': 'jquery-private' },

        // 'jquery-private' wants the real jQuery module
        // though. If this line was not here, there would
        // be an unresolvable cyclic dependency.
        'jquery-private': { 'jquery': 'jquery' }
    }
});
```

after you have done that, you will have to include the dependency for `jquery` everywhere you want to use it:

```
